# AtlasSeguros CRM — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Production CRM for an insurance broker agency in Spain.
Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict, PostgreSQL via Supabase.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode — zero any, zero ts-ignore)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Prisma + PostgreSQL (Supabase)
- NextAuth.js v5
- TanStack Table + TanStack Query
- React Hook Form + Zod
- Recharts
- Zustand (UI state only — never server state)
- date-fns (es-ES locale for all date formatting)
- AWS S3 pre-signed URLs
- Stripe
- Signaturit SDK
- Resend (emails only — invitations, password reset, offer rejected, contract activated)

## Absolute Rules — Never Break These

### Prisma
- Never import from `@prisma/client` directly in Server Actions or API routes
- Always import from `@/lib/prisma-client` (the extended client with RLS + soft-delete)
- Never hard-delete Lead, Client, or Offer — always set deletedAt = new Date()
- Never update or delete AuditLog or ConsentLog rows — append only
- Never update or delete OfferComment rows — append only

### Security
- Every Server Action that mutates data must be wrapped with withRole()
- Import withRole from @/lib/with-role
- Never trust role or userId from the request body — always read from session
- Password reset and invitation tokens: store only SHA-256 hash in DB, never raw token

### Commission Math (Phase A)
- Guard: if product.commissionUpfrontPct === 0 return [] immediately
- Gross = premiumAmount × commissionUpfrontPct
- Net = Gross - (Gross × feePct)
- Points = Net / 10
- Store points on Contract before running waterfall

### Commission Math (Phase C — Waterfall)
- Seller payout = points × sellerRateCard.euroPerPoint (isOverride: false)
- Each upline level: differential = managerRate - previousLevelRate
- If differential <= 0: skip (no payout for that level)
- If differential > 0: payout = points × differential (isOverride: true)
- Rate lookup: WHERE rankId = ? AND leadType = ? AND effectiveDate <= contract.createdAt
  ORDER BY effectiveDate DESC LIMIT 1

### UI Rules
- NO icons or emoticons anywhere — text labels only
- NO hardcoded colors — always use CSS variables (var(--color-*))
- All monetary values: Decimal type, 2 decimal places, never Float
- All dates: date-fns with es-ES locale
- Dark mode mandatory on every component

### Role Access
- ADMIN: invitations, partners, products, rateCards, documentTemplates, agents, audit log
- OPERATIONS: offer validation queue, contract activation, after-sales execution, Stripe monitoring
- AGENT: own leads/clients/offers, commissions, signatures — agentId = session.user.id always
- Manager agents (FA1-DN): own pipeline only in list queries — getDownlineAgentIds() for KPI aggregation ONLY

## Offer Status Machine
DRAFT → PENDING_OPERATIONS_REVIEW → SUBMITTED_TO_PARTNER → ACCEPTED
                                   ↘ REJECTED → (agent edits) → PENDING_OPERATIONS_REVIEW
CANCELLED and EXPIRED are terminal states.
ACCEPTED requires policyNumber + policyIssuedAt set by Operations.

## File Naming Conventions
- Server Actions: src/actions/[entity].ts
- Services: src/services/[name].service.ts
- Components: PascalCase — src/components/[module]/ComponentName.tsx
- Lib utilities: src/lib/[name].ts

## Key Files
- src/lib/prisma-client.ts — ONLY Prisma client to import in app code
- src/lib/with-role.ts — Server Action role guard
- src/lib/internal-ref.ts — CF-YYYY-NNNN reference generator
- src/lib/resend.ts — Resend email client
- src/services/commission.service.ts — CommissionService (never inline commission logic)
- src/services/audit.service.ts — AuditLog writes (use this, never write directly)

## AuditLog — Write on Every State Change For:
- Contract: CREATED, STATUS_CHANGED
- Offer: STATUS_CHANGED
- CommissionRecord: STATUS_CHANGED, AMOUNT_CHANGED, RECALCULATED
- Always include previousValue, newValue as JSON snapshots
- actorType: "agent" | "operations" | "admin" | "system" | "webhook"

## Email Templates (Resend + React Email)
Located in src/emails/
- invitation.tsx
- password-reset.tsx
- offer-rejected.tsx
- contract-activated.tsx

## What NOT to Do
- Never use useState for server data — use TanStack Query
- Never use Zustand for server data — Zustand is for UI state only (slide-overs, wizards)
- Never expose raw Stripe webhook without signature verification
- Never expose raw Signaturit webhook without HMAC verification
- Never generate CF-YYYY-NNNN with COUNT(*)+1 — use PostgreSQL sequence nextval()
- Never call CommissionService inline in Contract creation — always call explicitly after
- Never apply getDownlineAgentIds to client/lead list queries — KPI aggregation only
- Never render Operations or Admin UI components for Agent role (not even hidden)
- Never store files locally — always S3
## Third-Party Service Abstraction
- Payment calls: always through src/services/payment.service.ts — never import Stripe directly
- Signature calls: always through src/services/signature.service.ts — never import Signaturit directly
- This abstraction exists so providers can be swapped by replacing only the service file